<%- include("partials/header.ejs") %>

<div class="container">
  <div class="px-4 pt-5 my-5 text-center border-bottom">
    <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold text-body-emphasis">
      How to Play Pokémon TCG
    </h1>
    <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
      <p class="lead mb-4">
        Learn the basics of playing the Pokémon Trading Card Game with these
        step-by-step instructions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
      <!-- box 1-->
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Step 1: Get a Starter Deck</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            Purchase a Pokémon TCG starter deck. These decks contain everything
            you need to start playing, including a ready-to-play deck of cards,
            a rulebook, and other accessories.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- box 2-->
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Step 2: Learn the Basics</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            Familiarize yourself with the basic components of the game: Pokémon
            cards, Trainer cards, Energy cards, and the playing field (which
            consists of a deck, discard pile, bench, active Pokémon, and prize
            cards).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- box 3-->
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Step 3: Setup</h5>
          <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
            <li class="list-group-item">
              Shuffle your deck and draw seven cards. If you don't have any
              Basic Pokémon in your hand, reshuffle and draw again.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              Choose a Basic Pokémon from your hand to act as your Active
              Pokémon and place it face-down on the playmat.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              Place up to five Basic Pokémon on your Bench, also face-down.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Determine who goes first.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- box 4-->
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Step 4: Gameplay</h5>
          <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
            <li class="list-group-item">
              Draw a card from your deck at the beginning of your turn.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              Play Basic Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench if you have any.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              Attach an Energy card from your hand to one of your Pokémon per
              turn.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              Evolve your Pokémon if you have the corresponding Evolution cards.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              Use Trainer cards to support your Pokémon or disrupt your
              opponent.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              Attack your opponent's Active Pokémon using attacks listed on your
              Pokémon's card.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              Your opponent can use Trainer cards or Abilities in response, or
              switch their Active Pokémon with one on their Bench.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              If your Pokémon's HP reaches zero, it's knocked out, and your
              opponent takes one of your Prize cards.
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              The game continues until one player collects all their Prize cards
              or runs out of cards in their deck.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- box 5-->
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Step 5: Win Conditions</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            You win by either collecting all your Prize cards or if your
            opponent can't draw a card at the beginning of their turn.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- box 6-->
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Step 6: Advanced Strategies</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            As you become more experienced, you can experiment with
            deck-building strategies, card synergy, and advanced gameplay
            tactics.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- box 7-->
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Step 7: Keep Learning</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            Stay updated with the latest rule changes, card releases, and
            tournament formats by reading official Pokémon TCG resources and
            participating in local events or online communities.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- box 8-->
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Step 8: Have Fun!</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            The most important step! Enjoy the game, collect your favorite
            Pokémon cards, and have fun battling with friends and other players.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include("partials/footer.ejs") %>
